  <summary date="2009-08-19T18:01:14Z" status="Introduced in House">Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow affiliated life and non-life insurance companies to file consolidated tax returns.

Allows: (1) a phasein, between 2007 and 2013, of the full application of losses of affiliated non-life insurance companies against the taxable income of an affiliated life insurance company; and (2) an automatic waiver of the five-year waiting period applicable to affiliated non-life insurance companies for offset of their losses against life insurance company income.</summary>
